The Federal Executive Council (FEC) Wednesday approved N3.9billion variation for the construction of public housing for five subsisting secretariats in Anambra, Bayelsa, Osun, Nasarawa and Zamfara states.  The Minister of Works and Housing, Mr Babatunde Fashola addressing journalists at the end of the FEC meeting in Abuja said the sum changes the contract amount from N13.56billion to N17.54billion in total.  The FCT Minister, Mohammed Bello also disclosed that the Council approved an additional sum of N1.5billion bringing to total N2.53billion for the rehabilitation of Lower Usuma Dam Water Treatment Plant Phase Two in the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that FCT Minister said the contract awarded to Cupero Nigeria Ltd entails repairs and replacement of electro-mechanical components and laboratory restoration, rehabilitation of chemical and chlorine buildings, and general civil engineering work to be completed in 12months.